^C:CREDITS
:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Credits for individual WADs are provided on each page but where a mod is used broadly across many pages (such as enhancements, fixes and gameplay modifications), as best as is possible, a list of credits and sources is provided here. This information has been taken from whatever public sources are available; apologies for any mistakes.

(In alphabetical order:)


:Chocolate Doom / Heretic / Hexen / Strife - <chocolate-doom.org>
:===============================================================================
_Chocolate Doom_ is written by <Simon Howard>, with extensive help from many other people who have provided patches, bug reports and suggestions.

_Chocolate Strife_ was developed by <James Haley> and <Samuel Villarreal> as part of a painstaking reverse engineering project.

:Crispy Doom - <github.com/fabiangreffrath/crispy-doom>
:===============================================================================
"_Crispy Doom_ is a friendly fork of _Chocolate Doom_ that provides a higher display resolution, removes the static limits of the `Doom` engine and offers further optional visual, tactical and physical enhancements while remaining entirely config file, savegame, netplay and demo compatible with the original".

By <Fabian Greffrath>.

